	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />so BSNES would be the emulator that is the most accurate when it comes down to real SNES hardware?
<br />
<br />As for the flash cart at Tototek, if I understand how they work, you plug them in your PC, transfer the file and then it's plug-n-play in your regular SNES? Would a flash cart like that support games that uses advanced chips like let's say Starfox 2?
<br />
<br />Thank you for your reply.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
